UMUAHIA â€“ Abia State Governor Alex Otti has named the first set of his kitchen cabinet, bringing on board an academic, Prof Kenneth Kalu as Secretary to the State Government (SSG), Dr Pastor Caleb Ajagba, as Chief of Staff and Mr Ferdinand Ekeoma as his Special Adviser on Media and Publicity. A statement signed by Ekeoma Tuesday evening named other appointees as Mr.Kazie Ukoh, Chief Press Secretary, Dr Ngozi Okoronkwo, Special Adviser on Health Care Delivery Services, Mrs. Njum Onyemenam, Accountant General of the state and Mr. Ogbonnia Okereke, Head, Special Task Force on Emergency Cleanup of Aba and Umuahia. According to the statement, the appointments are with immediate effect.